I also know HTML and CSS, and this website is my first project in web-development. As of now, all my knowledge in computer science is self-taught. I learnt all of this over the summer after my highschool graduation. As this might suggest, I am an extremely committed and a fast learner; I give my 100% to any task I am handed. For instance, I basically learnt HTML and CSS in one week, while handling all of schoolwork and making this website. I went to a workshop hosted by a student group (Builds), where I was first introduced to web development. They taught us how to set up the basic framework of a website, and I was so fascinated by it that I moved on to learn HTML and build this website that week.
